Wildebeests have an affinity for their fellow herd  
animals, such as the plains zebra, the Thomson's  
gazelle, and the giraffe.  
 
The wildebeest is the preferred prey of lions,  
although far more are killed by the spotted hyena.  
When threatened, the wildebeest will give a short  
alarm snort that alerts the herd to trouble. Other  
large predators and non-native animals will cause  
the wildebeest to become uncomfortable. 
 
